blogs.title: The workings of the Gal bladder juice
blogs.content:
The Gal bladder secrets a juice called bile and this juice is secreted into the Liver. The juice serves multiple roles in the human body and if you are not informed enough, buckle up. What exactly do you know? What exactly do you wanna know?

The process called fat emulsification is coordinated by the bile. A simple example is like placing cheese on fire. Bile juice generates heat in the body and then burns and liquifies all the fat content it gets in contact with.
